main event: A witness observed two objects, one round and one shaped like a boomerang, in the sky over Trout Run, Pennsylvania on May 2, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were seen for 1 1/2 hours, appearing as lights in the sky,The round object maneuvered over a period of 4 1/2 hours,The witness described the first object as white and silhouetted against the sky,The sighting was classified as insufficient data due to being a single witness case,It was suggested that the observed phenomena might have been a light reflection from a stationary source.
sighted object: one round object and one boomerang-shaped object
witness description: A civilian who was driving home from work at night.
